cast.name: ‎玛尔塔·杜塞尔多普‎ Marta Dusseldorp

this_title: Australia's Ocean Odyssey: A Journey Down the East Australian Current Season 1
introduction: Hidden in our oceans are great rivers of seawater called ocean currents. These are the arteries and veins of planet Earth - a life support system that has helped regulate the Earth’s climate, atmosphere and biological diversity for millions of years.Journey with migrating humpback whales as they travel the length of the East Australian Current and explore the incredible diversity of Australia’s submarine ecosystems. From the corals of the Great Barrier Reef, through the kelp gardens of the New South Wales coast, right down to the Southern Ocean, Australia’s Ocean Odyssey reveals how ocean currents create life on our planet, and what we can all do to protect our planet’s blue heart.Episodes include…1. The Tropics2. The Sub-Tropical Zone3. The Temperate Zone
